==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Quitrent
<hw>Quit"rent`</hw> <pr>(kw⟦icr⟧t"r⟦ecr⟧nt`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Quit</ets>, a. + <ets>rent</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>A rent reserved in grants of land, by the payment of which the
tenant is quit from other service.</def>
<rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In some of the United States a fee-farm rent is so
termed.</note> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quits</ent>⟦br⟧
